✨S𝕖𝕝𝕗 C𝕒𝕣𝕖 R𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. W𝕣𝕚𝕥𝕖 A G𝕣𝕒𝕥𝕚𝕥𝕦𝕕𝕖 L𝕚𝕤𝕥
Sometimes we can get so busy and caught up in life that we forget to practice gratitude. It could be a person, a conversation, a kind gesture or the little things that make you smile it sitting and writing all these things down, however big or small can bring a sense of grounding as it shifts our minds to the present moment. It also allows us to take control of our thoughts. 

2. S𝕪𝕟𝕔 𝕨𝕚𝕥𝕙 𝕥𝕙𝕖 M𝕠𝕠𝕟
The moon is a powerful celestial body that reflects the flow of our lives and the phases we go through. With the full moon coming up, it’s a great time to reconnect. The full moon is when the moon is at the height of its power. Notice how it makes you feel. Start following the different phases of the moon as you move through the next 30 days. Research how the energies of the different phases can be used in you own life. 

3. T𝕒𝕜𝕖 𝕒 W𝕒𝕝𝕜
Go for a nature walk is a great way to get some exercise for your physical body but also to nourish mind and spirit too. Set some time aside each day to go for a walk, even if it’s just a short walk, it can boost your sense of well-being. Journal how this time makes you feel & the revelations & thoughts that come to you as a result. Notice how even a short walk can bring a sense of balance and can be incredibly grounding, which is important to us all, particularly if you’re an empath. Shake it up by visiting somewhere you haven’t been before to keep things interesting.

Leo season starts today! ✨
It is all about seeing friends, building up your confidence but this season is also connected to our pride. If you accidentally make someone feel as though they've been disrespected, it might be hard to sort things out. So be careful of the drama that can rise up throughout this time! 

Fire signs Aries, Leo, and Sagittarius will thrive the most during Leo season while fixed signs Taurus, Scorpio, and Aquarius could face a few challenges.

My Descendant is in Leo. Who has Leo somewhere in their birth chart?

🌿 E𝕤𝕤𝕖𝕟𝕥𝕚𝕒𝕝 O𝕚𝕝 𝕗𝕠𝕣 C𝕒𝕝𝕞 🌿
Here’s a selection of essential oils that bring their own kind of calming effect, whether it be used for meditation, relaxation or to help foster a sense of inner harmony. My favourite always has to be lavender, I definitely have a soft spot for it in all its forms!

It’s important undiluted essential oils are not used directly on the skin as they can seriously irritate it. They must be diluted by a carrier oil like grape seed or sunflower oil first. As I rule, I use 5-6 drops of essential oil for 1 fl oz/230mls of carrier oil, which gives you a decent sized batch.

What’s your favourite essential oil?

Lindsay 💜

✨𝕋𝕒𝕣𝕠𝕥 ℝ𝕖𝕧𝕖𝕒𝕝 ✨ 
1. The Eight of Elixirs (Cups) is an invitation to explore new realms. Sometimes in life things might not work out the way we hoped and letting go seems the only option. Removing those things in your life that doesn’t align with your highest purpose is essential. See this as an opportunity to learn and grown! Letting go doesn’t have to be a negative thing, it’s also a chance to ask yourself what brings you fulfilment and contentment and to follow them. It’s a time to explore what makes you truly happy so you can realign your direction with your passion. 

2. The Four of Candles (Wands) can indicate something much like a homecoming to the places and/or people who love and care for you. In numerology, four represents stability and safety, and this is the place your moving to. It’s an invitation to slow down and even pause. You’ve achieved so much, more than your realise, and now is the time to celebrate how far you’ve come and give yourself the credit you deserve.

3. The Moon is a reminder not to take everything at face value. Sometimes we only know half a story and don’t have all the information you need to move forward. Listen to your intuition so you can see beyond what’s in front of you. Feel into situations rather thinking what they mean. Let go of negative self talk and allow your intuition to guide you and give you a greater level of understanding. Feel into situations rather than overthinking what they might mean. Pay attention to your dreams, they can also give you guidance about which direction to go.
